subSubSection.paragraph:
11-12 mm; weight 4-6-5 g. Condylo-incisive lengths are 16-6-18 mm. The Cyrenaica White-toothed Shrew is small and looks like a small form of the European Lesser White-toothed Shrew (
C. suaveolens
), with short (c.2 mm) soft pelage and relatively long tail (¢.70% of head-body length). Dorsum is grayish brown, with slight russet tinge; hairs are dark and have gray bases. Venteris gray to grayish brown, with smooth transition zone; hairs have dark gray bases and gray to pale brown tips. Chin, throat, and chest are gray. Forefeet and hindfeet are brown. Tail is brown above and slightly paler below, with ¢.90% pilosity. Skull is unspecialized: rostrum and maxillary are medium, interorbit is wide, braincase width is medium, and braincase heightis high. I' is long and hooked, and upper third molar is wide. Karyotype is 2n = 40.
